index.html.title: JaHMIn
index.html.name: JaHMIn
index.html.summary: A Javascript framework to build Human Machine Interfaces for IoT

DataCommsEngine.html.title: DataCommsEngine
DataCommsEngine.html.name: DataCommsEngine
DataCommsEngine.html.description: Abstract class defining a Comunication Engine for data I/O with a server.

DataCommsEngine.html#toBeSubscribed.title: toBeSubscribed
DataCommsEngine.html#toBeSubscribed.name: toBeSubscribed
DataCommsEngine.html#toBeSubscribed.description: Variables waiting to be subscribed for updates. It is a key-number map. The number represent how many UI element times requested updates from that variable. Variables are purged once subscribed. If subscription fails with "NO-NET" or "CANT-SUB" error the var is kept for later subscription, if fails with "WONT-SUB" or "NOT-EXIST" it will be purged from list.

DataCommsEngine.html#toBeUnsubscribed.title: toBeUnsubscribed
DataCommsEngine.html#toBeUnsubscribed.name: toBeUnsubscribed
DataCommsEngine.html#toBeUnsubscribed.description: List of Variables waiting to be unsubscribed from updates.

DataCommsEngine.html#subscribedVar.title: subscribedVar
DataCommsEngine.html#subscribedVar.name: subscribedVar
DataCommsEngine.html#subscribedVar.description: List of Variables currently subscribed for updates. It is a key-number map. The number represent the number of UI-elements registered with the same variable, usually one, but for special cases could be more.

DataCommsEngine.html#aggregationTime_ms.title: aggregationTime_ms
DataCommsEngine.html#aggregationTime_ms.name: aggregationTime_ms
DataCommsEngine.html#aggregationTime_ms.description: Time the system will wait before sending subscruiption/unsubscription, so that variable can be aggregated and make moreefficient network calls.

DataCommsEngine.html#UpdateData.title: UpdateData( data )
DataCommsEngine.html#UpdateData.name: UpdateData
DataCommsEngine.html#UpdateData.description: Action Update. It updates a list of variable values and statuses in the DataManager. The updates will be automatically dispatched to all UI component connected to those variables.

DataTree.html.title: DataTree
DataTree.html.name: DataTree
DataTree.html.description: Class that contains all the variable of the App for all the subsystem. It is connected automatically to UI element and schedule updates on them.

DataTree.html#GetVar.title: GetVar( varID )
DataTree.html#GetVar.name: GetVar
DataTree.html#GetVar.description: Get the current value and status of the related stateVariable. It returns a proxy to the real stateVariable, this is readonly, as a protection it will throw if you try to assign a value.

DataTree.html#Update.title: Update( variables )
DataTree.html#Update.name: Update
DataTree.html#Update.description: It upadtes with the variable or the list of variables. This will automatically call UI update of all connected elements.

DataTree.html#ExistVar.title: ExistVar( varID )
DataTree.html#ExistVar.name: ExistVar
DataTree.html#ExistVar.description: Checks if the variable exist in the current state tree

systemError.html.title: systemError
systemError.html.name: systemError
systemError.html.description: Describe a system error occurred during a requested Action (like subscribe, write, etc.).

systemVariable.html.title: systemVariable
systemVariable.html.name: systemVariable
systemVariable.html.description: Defines a generic variable bound to a specific system. The "value" must be a JSON compatible object, since these values are persisted in localstorage. So anything is good but functions.
